TITLE: 'Light on the truth': Gabbard announces RFK files released months after Trump's order
SUMMARY: DNI Director Tulsi Gabbard announced the release of the first batch of Robert F. Kennedy assassination files on Friday after having previously teased the news during a cabinet meeting earlier this month.

TITLE: Top GOP lawmaker, Hochul trade barbs amid speculation Trump ally is jumping in gubernatorial race
SUMMARY: New York Gov. Kathy Hochul and Rep. Elise Stefanik, R-N.Y., have already begun trading barbs in the 2026 gubernatorial race amid reports that the Republican congresswoman is considering a run.

TITLE: White House photo bluntly shows where parties stand on immigration amid Abrego Garcia deportation
SUMMARY: The White House releases contrasting images showing Trump comforting grieving mother Patty Morin while Democrat senator Van Hollen meets with deported illegal immigrant in El Salvador.

TITLE: Top Dem asks Noem how TSA will prevent 'major disruptions' as many travelers still lack REAL ID
SUMMARY: Democrat Sen. Jack Reed of Rhode Island sent a letter to DHS Secretary Kristi Noem asking for a contingency plan in case travelers get stranded due to the REAL ID mandate.

TITLE: Federal judge bucks Trump admin, delays dismissal of of MS-13 leader's case
SUMMARY: A federal judge blocked the Trump administration from dropping charges against alleged MS-13 leader Henrry Villatoro Santos, ordering he remain in U.S. custody for now.

TITLE: Huckabee visits iconic holy site in Israel, delivers Trump's prayer for peace
SUMMARY: U.S. Ambassador to Israel Mike Huckabee delivered a prayer from President Donald Trump to a major holy site in Jerusalem as Passover ends and Easter approaches.

TITLE: Confidence in Congressional Democrats hits all time low in new poll
SUMMARY: A new national poll shows that confidence in Democratic Party leaders in Congress has hit an all-time low. This as the party's favorable ratings have sunk to historic lows in other surveys

TITLE: LGBTQ Christians crusade against Trump's religiously 'hostile' policies during Holy Week
SUMMARY: Attendees at the Collective of Queer Christian Leaders event in Washington told Fox News Digital they reject President Donald Trump.

TITLE: Trump calls Sen. Van Hollen a 'fool' after meeting with deported MS-13 suspect in El Salvador
SUMMARY: President Donald Trump is calling Sen. Chris Van Hollen a "fool" after the Maryland Democrat flew to El Salvador to meet with Kilmar Abrego Garcia.

TITLE: Trump announces a conservative media star, a GOP governor, and others for Homeland Security Advisory Council
SUMMARY: President Donald Trump taps Mark Levin, South Carolina Gov. Henry McMaster, former NYPD detective Bo Dietl and Florida state Sen. Joe Gruters to serve on Homeland Security Advisory Council

TITLE: Poll position: How Trump's approval rating compares to his presidential predecessors
SUMMARY: Where President Donald Trump's approval ratings stands in a new nation poll, and where he stands in comparison to his White House predecessors during their first three months in office

TITLE: Top GOP senator calls out Code Pink, The People’s Forum allegedly pushing CCP propaganda in US
SUMMARY: Sen. Charles Grassley, R-Iowa, is asking the Department of Justice to look into whether two left-wing groups should have to register under FARA.

TITLE: Biden's vax-focused COVID-19 website obliterated by White House, replaced with 'true origins' virus guide
SUMMARY: The White House rolled out a new COVID.gov website showing the “true origins" of the coronavirus after Democrats and the media discredited the lab-leak theory.

TITLE: ICE arrests over 200 illegal aliens in New York City's 'most crime-infested neighborhoods'
SUMMARY: ICE arrested over 200 illegal aliens in an “enhanced immigration enforcement operation" in the “most crime-infested neighborhoods" in and around New York City in just one week.

TITLE: ICE and DOGE seek sensitive data in crackdown on illegal immigration, waste: report
SUMMARY: As the Trump administration cracks down on illegal immigration and government waste, ICE and DOGE reportedly seek sensitive data allegedly to track down individuals.

TITLE: HHS probing hospital over firing of nurse who blew whistle on minors getting gender treatments
SUMMARY: HHS is investigating a hospital after a nurse who sought a religious exemption to avoid administering puberty blockers and cross-sex hormones to children was fired.

TITLE: Radical activist who fueled Cori Bush's campaigns emerges as spokesperson for track star's murder suspect
SUMMARY: A spokesperson for the family of the 17-year-old boy accused of stabbing a teen track star to death has a long history of supporting defunding the police as well as close ties to a former 'Squad' Democrat.

TITLE: Rubio says US ready to 'move on' within days if no progress made on Russia-Ukraine peace deal
SUMMARY: Sec. of State Marco Rubio warns U.S. will cease efforts to secure peace between Russia and Ukraine if the effort does not appear achieveable in the short term

TITLE: Federal judge temporarily restricts DOGE access to personalized Social Security data
SUMMARY: An Obama-appointed judge in Baltimore issued a preliminary injunction Thursday restricting the Department of Government Efficiency’s access to Social Security data.

TITLE: Trump: China calling ‘a lot’ since last week's tariff increase, deal could happen as soon as 3 weeks
SUMMARY: Reporters ask President Trump about the status of his negotiations with China and, in particular, whether he has spoken to Chinese President Xi Jinping amid the ongoing trade war.

TITLE: Bribery trial of Nadine Menendez reaches closing arguments: 'Partner in crime'
SUMMARY: Nadine Menendez, the wife of former U.S. Sen. Bob Menendez, sat quietly in the courtroom as prosecutors and defense attorneys delivered closing arguments today in her bribery trial.

TITLE: Dem Senator Van Hollen meets, shakes hands with Abrego Garcia; El Salvador says inmate will remain in custody
SUMMARY: Democratic Sen. Chris Van Hollen of Maryland met with Kilmar Abrego Garcia on Thursday in El Salvador after being denied access to the inmate multiple times.

TITLE: Letitia James launches high-dollar fundraiser after alleged mortgage fraud case
SUMMARY: New York Attorney General Letitia James launches an ActBlue fundraiser seeking donations up to $18K-per-person in wake of alleged mortgage fraud.

TITLE: HUD puts half-occupied headquarters building in DC up for sale
SUMMARY: HUD's headquarters was put on a list of federal assets to be sold, and it is facing hundreds of millions in deferred maintenance costs with only half the building being used.

TITLE: Supreme Court poised to make major decision that could set limits on the power of district judges
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court has agreed to examine the Trump administration’s challenge to judges issuing nationwide injunctions.
